snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Step into Jethalal‚Äôs world with Gada Electronics!  Manage the shop, tackle quirky customers, and experience nonstop TMKOC-style fun. 

Are you ready for the challenge? 
Play now: https://gadaelectronics.page.link/dhgB  
#GadaElectronics #TMKOCGame

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

Click here to watch NEW Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSxhJ6UCi6tgujD-FsAy0sw

Click here to watch your favourite videos from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: 
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

snippet.title: Brahmanandam Speech| Kannappa Pre Release Event- Hyderabad | Vishnu Manchu | Prabhas
snippet.description:

In his unique style, Brahmanandam shared his excitement about Kannappa, praised the team led by Vishnu Manchu, and entertained the audience with his wit and charm. Don‚Äôt miss this delightful moment from the grand event!

üé¨ Get ready for the epic release of Kannappa on 27th June 2025 worldwide!

snippet.title: Iran Launches Revenge Attack After US Strike: Israel Panics Amid Huge Missile Salvo- First In 24 Hrs
snippet.description:
Hours after US bombed Iran's nuclear sites, Tehran launched revenge attacks on Israel, targeting major cities. Sirens rang out in central and northern Israel as a fresh salvo of Iranian missiles was detected by the Israeli military. Iran had warned of consequences if US attacked its nuclear facilities. Watch the video for more details.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Some scientists claim to have captured a strange glowing phenomenon, something like an aura emerging from the human body using their instruments. You might‚Äôve seen viral reports on the internet suggesting this too. But what exactly is this mysterious light that appears in living beings but vanishes after death and that isn‚Äôt just body heat?

This very question intrigued a brilliant Japanese scientist, Masaki Kobayashi from Tohoku University, back in 2009. To find the answer, he conducted a groundbreaking experiment on this so-called ‚Äúhuman light‚Äù. Little did he know, his discovery would shake the way we perceive reality.

Interestingly, many scientists at the time believed no scientific evidence could ever prove the existence of a soul or consciousness and they conducted experiments to support that view. But Masaki wasn‚Äôt fully convinced. What did he know about this mysterious light that others didn‚Äôt? So, was Masaki Kobayashi just measuring light, or was he witnessing something far deeper?
Is this strange glow just a biological glitch, or the first glimpse of the human soul?
And if something truly leaves the body when we die, what exactly are we?

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Nitish Bhaluni / Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu)

snippet.title: GAANJI - Official Music Video | Chandan Shetty | Folk x Fusion
snippet.description:
From North Karnataka to the World: A Folk Song Reimagined Through Dance. Having zero expectations and a full heart, I present to you this experimental music video ‚Äî a piece of art born from a deeply personal journey.

I composed this song nine years ago, inspired by a beloved folk rhyme from North Karnataka. Over time, its melody stayed close to me, quietly asking to be brought to life in a new form.

The visual inspiration comes from a range of minimalistic music videos, especially those shot on white-screen backgrounds (like ‚ÄòSorry‚Äô from Justin Bieber). I finally started working on the video in 2023, and just two months ago, we brought it to life.

We held virtual auditions across India, and with the brilliant support of choreographers Praveen Veigas,  Pushpa, and Muskan, we selected 10 incredible dancers who brought their energy and magic to this performance.

This project would not have been possible without the dedication and brilliance of a phenomenal team:
        ‚Ä¢        Co-Producer: Greeshma Gowda
        ‚Ä¢        DOP: Suhas Amin
        ‚Ä¢        Editor & VFX: Dheeraj Poojary
        ‚Ä¢        Programming, Mixing & Mastering: Agastya Raag
        ‚Ä¢       Dancers: Alina Khan, Yukta, Muskan, Chaitanya, Payal, Jaquline, Sana, Shivani, Sneha.
        ‚Ä¢       Chorus: Mahalakshmi, Harismaran . A, Harshit N.U, Siri B.S, Prerana Navalgi, Nikisha H.A, Sana .S, Meghana Saishree, Shivani .S, Kshama .D Raj, Sanchita Vinay, M. Madhumitha, Dhriti Vishwanath, Isha .V, Omkar Kumble, Ghanashyam G.R, Tanav .S, Arav G.A, Ruchitha .V, Ridhima .K, Pranathi .V, Panvi N.U.
        ‚Ä¢      Poster Design : Ankith Anil 
        ‚Ä¢      Digitally Distributed by A3 Labels
        ‚Ä¢      Digital Promotions: Digital Magnet Media - Dhanu Krishnaa


To all the technicians and artists involved ‚Äî your work has been outstanding, and I deeply appreciate each one of you.

This video is directed by Chandan Shetty, and represents not just a song, but a dream nurtured over time.

I truly hope you connect with it, feel the spirit behind it, and show it some love.

Listen on your favorite platform:

Jio Saavn:https://www.jiosaavn.com/song/gaanji/Oxwgfyd0VXI

localized.title: GAANJI - Official Music Video | Chandan Shetty | Folk x Fusion
localized.description:
From North Karnataka to the World: A Folk Song Reimagined Through Dance. Having zero expectations and a full heart, I present to you this experimental music video ‚Äî a piece of art born from a deeply personal journey.

I composed this song nine years ago, inspired by a beloved folk rhyme from North Karnataka. Over time, its melody stayed close to me, quietly asking to be brought to life in a new form.

The visual inspiration comes from a range of minimalistic music videos, especially those shot on white-screen backgrounds (like ‚ÄòSorry‚Äô from Justin Bieber). I finally started working on the video in 2023, and just two months ago, we brought it to life.

We held virtual auditions across India, and with the brilliant support of choreographers Praveen Veigas,  Pushpa, and Muskan, we selected 10 incredible dancers who brought their energy and magic to this performance.

This project would not have been possible without the dedication and brilliance of a phenomenal team:
        ‚Ä¢        Co-Producer: Greeshma Gowda
        ‚Ä¢        DOP: Suhas Amin
        ‚Ä¢        Editor & VFX: Dheeraj Poojary
        ‚Ä¢        Programming, Mixing & Mastering: Agastya Raag
        ‚Ä¢       Dancers: Alina Khan, Yukta, Muskan, Chaitanya, Payal, Jaquline, Sana, Shivani, Sneha.
        ‚Ä¢       Chorus: Mahalakshmi, Harismaran . A, Harshit N.U, Siri B.S, Prerana Navalgi, Nikisha H.A, Sana .S, Meghana Saishree, Shivani .S, Kshama .D Raj, Sanchita Vinay, M. Madhumitha, Dhriti Vishwanath, Isha .V, Omkar Kumble, Ghanashyam G.R, Tanav .S, Arav G.A, Ruchitha .V, Ridhima .K, Pranathi .V, Panvi N.U.
        ‚Ä¢      Poster Design : Ankith Anil 
        ‚Ä¢      Digitally Distributed by A3 Labels
        ‚Ä¢      Digital Promotions: Digital Magnet Media - Dhanu Krishnaa


To all the technicians and artists involved ‚Äî your work has been outstanding, and I deeply appreciate each one of you.

This video is directed by Chandan Shetty, and represents not just a song, but a dream nurtured over time.

I truly hope you connect with it, feel the spirit behind it, and show it some love.

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

snippet.description:

Watch the FULL MOVIE of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzSk2_rPKNCDcjNAA8vaDN-E&si=rC5AotwLD2r3MHna

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta', is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' and a mischievous son 'Tapu'. Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalal' to call his father 'Champaklal' from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues that are socially relevant.
